title: Did Woman Who Died at Capitol Riot Carry a ‘Don’t Tread on Me’ Flag?
subtitle: Macabre online speculation surrounded the death of Georgia resident Rosanne Boyland during the Jan. 6, 2021, U.S. Capitol riots.
author: Dan MacGuill
vclaim: Rosanne Boyland was trampled to death at the U.S. Capitol riot in January 2021 after carrying a Gadsden flag that read "Don't tread on me."
